clauses.description: Extended final age 3a for lump-sum tariffs
clauses.text:
The policyholder
- acknowledges that their contract may be valid for a maximum of five years after reaching retirement age. In order for the contract to remain valid, the policyholder must be employed with an income subject to AHV contributions during this period. If the policyholder gives up employment, they must inform Generali immediately.
- confirms that they will surrender the insurance immediately (at the end of the month in which they give up employment) if they give up employment after reaching retirement age. The calculation date for the surrender value is the first day of the month after the written request for surrender has been received. If the surrender date is the first day of a month, this will be the calculation date, and the previous day will be the date when the contract ends. Surrender is also mandatory if the insurance is premium-free.
- acknowledges that if they surrender the policy before the contractually agreed expiry date because they have stopped working after reaching ordinary retirement age:
o in the case of fund-linked insurance with a guaranteed survival benefit or conventional insurance, at least the guaranteed surrender value is paid out.
o in the case of fund-linked insurance without a guaranteed survival benefit, no guaranteed minimum amount is specified. The surrender value is calculated from the fund assets minus the non-amortised acquisition costs.
o in the case of death benefits insurance, the inventory reserve minus the non-amortised acquisition costs is paid out as the surrender value.
